label.value: TMPRSS2 cutting open S protein of SARS-CoV-2

definition.value: A SARS-CoV-2 viral process in which after a SARS-CoV-2 virion attaches to a target cell, the cell's protease TMPRSS2 cuts open the spike protein of the virus, exposing a fusion peptide in the S2 subunit, and the host receptor ACE2.
A SARS-CoV-2 viral process that causes the fusion of host cells into multinucleated syncytal complexes.
A host-coronavirus interaction process that is implemented by the virus

label.value: cytokine storm response to SARS-CoV-2 infection

definition.value: Cytokine storm is considered to be one of the major causes of Acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) and multiple-organ failure, which often occur rapidly and resulted in death of COVID-19 patients within a short time. Cytokine storm plays an important role in the process of disease aggravation. Ref: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7194613/
A coronavirus process that involves in the release of the assemblied virion from the host cell

label.value: coronaviral molecular interaction inside host cell

definition.value: A host-coronavirus molecular interaction where the focus is the coronavirus process inside a host cell at the molecular level.
A coronavirus molecular interaction that results in the synthesis of viral structure protein

label.value: hydrolysis of angiotensin II into angiotensin (1-7)

definition.value: hydrolysis of angiotensin II into angiotensin (1-7) by ACE2
A SARS-CoV-2 variant virus that has a signature variant ORF8-L84S.
Clade L is the reference genome that was found at the beginning of the COVID-19 pandemic (December 2019).
A SARS-CoV-2 variant virus that has signature mutation in Spike D614G.
Sequencing efforts, mostly located in North America and Europe,  demonstrated an ever-increasing frequency of G, GH, and GR genomes. Reference: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7387429/
A SARS-CoV-2 variant virus that has a signature variant of the ORF3a coding protein NS3-G251.
A SARS-CoV-2 clade G variant virus that has signature mutations in Spike D614G and ORF3a Q57H.
The vastly prevalent genome in North America is clade GH. Reference: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7387429/
A SARS-CoV-2 clade G variant virus that carries the combination of Spike D614G and Nucleocapsid RG203KR mutations.

In Europe and South America, the most frequent clades are clade GR. This clde GR is is currently the most common representative of the SARS-CoV-2 population worldwide. Reference: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7387429/
a SARS-CoV-2 virus that belongs to clade O, which stands for "Other", meaning it is not G, GH, GR, L, S, or V.
An AA variant that occurs in a SARS-CoV-2 viral proteome
A SARS-CoV-2 amino acid variant that is located at the position 614 in the Wuhan reference strain S protein, and has been changed from D in the reference protein to the G residue.

The Spike D614G amino acid change is caused by an A-to-G nucleotide mutation at position 23,403 (A23403G) in the Wuhan reference strain; it was the only site identified in our first Spike variation analysis in early March 2020 that met our threshold criterion.
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7387429/
An aa-changing SNP variant of G25563T that occurs in the ORF3a protein of a SARS-CoV-2 virus. It is a characteristic mutation of SARS-CoV-2 clade GH.

An aa-changing SNP triplet GGG28881AAC that occurs in a Nucleocapsid protein of a SARS-CoV-2 virus. This mutations AA at positions in 203 and 204 into lysine and arginene. It is a signature variant of SARS-CoV-2 clade GR.
An aa-changing SNP triplet GGG28881AAC that occurs in a Nucleocapsid protein of a SARS-CoV-2 virus.It is a signature variant of SARS-CoV-2 clade GR.
ORF8-L84S is SNP variant that occurs at T28144C at ORF8 protein, which is shown in a SARS-CoV-2 clade S variant virus.
ORF3a:G251V
an aa-changing SNP variant that occurs at G26144T at ORF3a protein of SARS-CoV-2 virus. It is a signature variation in SARS-CoV clade V.

A chemical entity that is an amino acid variant in a coronavirus proteome. Such an amino acid variant is defined as a substittion of amino acid residues. Such a variant is defined by comparing with the reference strain of the coronavirus. For example, D614G is a SARS-CoV-2 coronoviral amino acid variant that has the change from D to G at the position 614 compared with the reference Wuhan strain.
